<title>USA: Raytheon files $3 billion shelf.</title>
<headline>Raytheon files $3 billion shelf.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Raytheon Co filed a shelf registration with the Securities and Exchange Commission on Friday to sell up to $3 billion in debt securities, preferred and common stock.</p>
<p>The net proceeds will be used to finance the acquisition of HE Holdings Inc, a subisidiary of General Motors Corp, working capital requirements and for other general corporate purposes.</p>
<p>Raytheon previously filed a shelf registration with the SEC for $875 million.</p>
<p>The international high technology company is based in Lexington, Mass. The business is centered on commercial and defense electronics, engineering and construction, aircraft and major applicances.</p>
